Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EnvironmentInterface
    This interface unifies the control classes ("environments") of the simulator and the player making it possible to use the same View object in both applications with only minor modifications.
    ModelInterface
    Interface the common access to simulation and replay models
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Agent
    The Agent class hold all information about agents in the system and is responsible for the coloring and energy management of the agents.
    CSVLog
    Class for logging the agent energy levels into Excel readable CSV file.
    EnergyBarListener
    This class handles mouse events from the energy bar part of the GUI
    EnergyBars
    This class extends the Canvas class implementing all drawing operations to display the agent energy bars on the right side of the main frame.
    Food
    This class stores all values about food object in the game.
    GameConfig
    This class allows access to the settings in the configuration file specified in the mas2j file as paramter of the GameEnvironment
    GameEnvironment
    The main class of the AgentGame, extending the built in TimeSteppedEnvironment.
    GameMap
    The map class handling position based tasks
    GameModel
    Model of the world in the game.
    GameView
    The GUI object of the application displaying the OpenGL powered world view
    Player
    The controller class of the player application
    Position
    Class representing positions in the game.
    ReplayModel
    The model of the player
    RoundLog
    Class for logging the states of the game step by step.
    SummaryGraphs
    This class records and displays summary data
    Team
    The team class represents the team of agents belonging to the same player.
    Updater  
    Watchdog
    The class looking for frozen simulation if no GUI is enabled
    Water
    The class representing water objects on the map making agent movement more costly than usual.
